            's family, and got a little spot of paint on it, which is here now.</p>
               <p>Prisoner. Q. Did you ever set eyes on me before that morning? A. Yes, I had.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I never saw that woman till she was drinking with me in the gin-shop, and I asked what she was staring at.</p>
